{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KjFgAmr6Gw1zN6Cmkh4D22","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { describe, it } from \"mocha\";\n     2→import { expect } from \"chai\";\n     3→import { startAnchor, BankrunProvider } from \"anchor-bankrun\";\n     4→import { AnchorError, Program } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n     5→import { Wallet } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n     6→import {\n     7→  Keypair,\n     8→  PublicKey,\n     9→  SystemProgram,\n    10→  LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    11→} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    12→import { Clock } from \"solana-bankrun\";\n    13→import type { Lordofrngs } from \"../target/types/lordofrngs\";\n    14→import { readFileSync } from \"fs\";\n    15→import { dirname, join } from \"path\";\n    16→import { fileURLToPath } from \"url\";\n    17→import BN from \"bn.js\";\n    18→\n    19→const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\n    20→const __dirname = dirname(__filename);\n    21→\n    22→const IDL = JSON.parse(\n    23→  readFileSync(join(__dirname, \"..\", \"target\", \"idl\", \"lordofrngs.json\"), \"utf8\")\n    24→);\n    25→const PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(IDL.address);\n    26→\n    27→// Tier constants (from shared crate)\n    28→const TIER_IRON = 0;\n    29→const TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL\n    30→const COUNTDOWN_SECONDS = 60;\n    31→\n    32→// Mock VRF randomness buffers (32 bytes each)\n    33→// Unfulfilled: all zeros → is_fulfilled=false\n    34→const RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED = Buffer.alloc(32);\n    35→\n    36→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    37→// PDA helpers\n    38→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    39→function getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n    40→  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    41→    [Buffer.from(\"lord_config\")],\n    42→    PROGRAM_ID\n    43→  );\n    44→  return pda;\n    45→}\n    46→\n    47→function getRoundPda(tier: number, roundNumber: number | bigint): PublicKey {\n    48→  const tierBuf = Buffer.from([tier]);\n    49→  const roundBuf = Buffer.alloc(8);\n    50→  roundBuf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(roundNumber));\n    51→  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    52→    [Buffer.from(\"jackpot_round\"), tierBuf, roundBuf],\n    53→    PROGRAM_ID\n    54→  );\n    55→  return pda;\n    56→}\n    57→\n    58→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    59→// Test context factory\n    60→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    61→function fundedAccountData(lamports = 100 * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL) {\n    62→  return {\n    63→    lamports,\n    64→    data: Buffer.alloc(0),\n    65→    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n    66→    executable: false,\n    67→  };\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→interface TestContext {\n    71→  context: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof startAnchor>>;\n    72→  creator: PublicKey;\n    73→  treasury: Keypair;\n    74→  creatorProgram: Program<Lordofrngs>;\n    75→  configPda: PublicKey;\n    76→  player2: Keypair;\n    77→  player2Program: Program<Lordofrngs>;\n    78→  mockRandomness: Keypair;\n    79→  mockOraoProgram: Keypair;\n    80→  mockOraoNetworkState: Keypair;\n    81→  mockOraoTreasury: Keypair;\n    82→}\n    83→\n    84→async function createTestContext(): Promise<TestContext> {\n    85→  const treasury = Keypair.generate();\n    86→  const player2 = Keypair.generate();\n    87→  const mockRandomness = Keypair.generate();\n    88→  const mockOraoProgram = Keypair.generate();\n    89→  const mockOraoNetworkState = Keypair.generate();\n    90→  const mockOraoTreasury = Keypair.generate();\n    91→\n    92→  const context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n    93→    { address: treasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n    94→    { address: player2.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n    95→    // Mock Orao accounts (UncheckedAccount, CPI is no-op under mock-vrf)\n    96→    { address: mockOraoProgram.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n    97→    { address: mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n    98→    { address: mockOraoTreasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n    99→    // Mock randomness account — starts unfulfilled (32 zero bytes)\n   100→    {\n   101→      address: mockRandomness.publicKey,\n   102→      info: {\n   103→        lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n   104→        data: RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED,\n   105→        owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n   106→        executable: false,\n   107→      },\n   108→    },\n   109→  ]);\n   110→\n   111→  const creatorProvider = new BankrunProvider(context);\n   112→  const creatorProgram = new Program<Lordofrngs>(IDL, creatorProvider);\n   113→\n   114→  const player2Provider = new BankrunProvider(context, new Wallet(player2));\n   115→  const player2Program = new Program<Lordofrngs>(IDL, player2Provider);\n   116→\n   117→  const creator = creatorProvider.wallet.publicKey;\n   118→  const configPda = getConfigPda();\n   119→\n   120→  return {\n   121→    context,\n   122→    creator,\n   123→    treasury,\n   124→    creatorProgram,\n   125→    configPda,\n   126→    player2,\n   127→    player2Program,\n   128→    mockRandomness,\n   129→    mockOraoProgram,\n   130→    mockOraoNetworkState,\n   131→    mockOraoTreasury,\n   132→  };\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   136→// Clock warp helpers\n   137→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   138→async function warpPastCountdown(t: TestContext) {\n   139→  const clock = await t.context.banksClient.getClock();\n   140→  t.context.setClock(\n   141→    new Clock(\n   142→      clock.slot + BigInt(200),\n   143→      clock.epochStartTimestamp,\n   144→      clock.epoch,\n   145→      clock.leaderScheduleEpoch,\n   146→      clock.unixTimestamp + BigInt(COUNTDOWN_SECONDS + 10)\n   147→    )\n   148→  );\n   149→}\n   150→\n   151→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   152→// Instruction helpers\n   153→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   154→async function initConfig(t: TestContext) {\n   155→  await t.creatorProgram.methods\n   156→    .initializeConfig(t.treasury.publicKey)\n   157→    .accounts({\n   158→      authority: t.creator,\n   159→      config: t.configPda,\n   160→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   161→    })\n   162→    .rpc();\n   163→}\n   164→\n   165→async function createRound(\n   166→  t: TestContext,\n   167→  tier = TIER_IRON,\n   168→  roundNumber = 0,\n   169→  numEntries = 1,\n   170→  creator?: PublicKey,\n   171→) {\n   172→  const roundPda = getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber);\n   173→  await t.creatorProgram.methods\n   174→    .createRound(tier, new BN(roundNumber), numEntries)\n   175→    .accounts({\n   176→      creator: creator ?? t.creator,\n   177→      config: t.configPda,\n   178→      round: roundPda,\n   179→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   180→    })\n   181→    .rpc();\n   182→  return roundPda;\n   183→}\n   184→\n   185→async function joinRound(\n   186→  program: Program<Lordofrngs>,\n   187→  player: PublicKey,\n   188→  configPda: PublicKey,\n   189→  tier = TIER_IRON,\n   190→  roundNumber = 0,\n   191→  numEntries = 1,\n   192→) {\n   193→  const roundPda = getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber);\n   194→  await program.methods\n   195→    .joinRound(tier, new BN(roundNumber), numEntries)\n   196→    .accounts({\n   197→      player,\n   198→      config: configPda,\n   199→      round: roundPda,\n   200→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   201→    })\n   202→    .rpc();\n   203→  return roundPda;\n   204→}\n   205→\n   206→async function buyMoreEntries(\n   207→  program: Program<Lordofrngs>,\n   208→  player: PublicKey,\n   209→  configPda: PublicKey,\n   210→  tier = TIER_IRON,\n   211→  roundNumber = 0,\n   212→  numEntries = 1,\n   213→) {\n   214→  const roundPda = getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber);\n   215→  await program.methods\n   216→    .buyMoreEntries(tier, new BN(roundNumber), numEntries)\n   217→    .accounts({\n   218→      player,\n   219→      config: configPda,\n   220→      round: roundPda,\n   221→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   222→    })\n   223→    .rpc();\n   224→  return roundPda;\n   225→}\n   226→\n   227→async function startSpin(\n   228→  program: Program<Lordofrngs>,\n   229→  caller: PublicKey,\n   230→  t: TestContext,\n   231→  tier = TIER_IRON,\n   232→  roundNumber = 0,\n   233→) {\n   234→  const roundPda = getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber);\n   235→  await program.methods\n   236→    .startSpin(tier, new BN(roundNumber))\n   237→    .accounts({\n   238→      caller,\n   239→      config: t.configPda,\n   240→      round: roundPda,\n   241→      oraoProgram: t.mockOraoProgram.publicKey,\n   242→      oraoNetworkState: t.mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey,\n   243→      oraoTreasury: t.mockOraoTreasury.publicKey,\n   244→      oraoRandom: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n   245→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   246→    })\n   247→    .rpc();\n   248→  return roundPda;\n   249→}\n   250→\n   251→// Fee constant (3% = 300 bps)\n   252→const TOTAL_FEE_BPS = 300;\n   253→\n   254→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   255→// Mock VRF + balance helpers\n   256→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   257→function setMockRandomness(t: TestContext, data: Buffer) {\n   258→  t.context.setAccount(t.mockRandomness.publicKey, {\n   259→    lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n   260→    data,\n   261→    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n   262→    executable: false,\n   263→  });\n   264→}\n   265→\n   266→async function getBalance(t: TestContext, pubkey: PublicKey): Promise<number> {\n   267→  const account = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(pubkey);\n   268→  return account ? Number(account.lamports) : 0;\n   269→}\n   270→\n   271→/**\n   272→ * Build randomness buffer where the first 8 bytes (as u64 LE) mod totalEntries\n   273→ * yields the desired winningSlot.\n   274→ */\n   275→function buildRandomness(winningSlot: number, totalEntries: number): Buffer {\n   276→  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n   277→  // Write winningSlot as u64 LE — since winningSlot < totalEntries, mod is identity\n   278→  buf.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(winningSlot));\n   279→  // Ensure at least one byte is non-zero so is_fulfilled returns true\n   280→  if (winningSlot === 0) buf[8] = 1;\n   281→  return buf;\n   282→}\n   283→\n   284→/**\n   285→ * Determine the winner from randomness, totalEntries, and players list.\n   286→ * Mirrors the on-chain logic: rand_u64 % total_entries → slot → owner.\n   287→ */\n   288→function deriveWinner(\n   289→  randomness: Buffer,\n   290→  totalEntries: number,\n   291→  players: Array<{ player: PublicKey; entries: number }>\n   292→): { winningSlot: number; winner: PublicKey } {\n   293→  const randU64 = randomness.readBigUInt64LE(0);\n   294→  const winningSlot = Number(randU64 % BigInt(totalEntries));\n   295→  let cumulative = 0;\n   296→  for (const entry of players) {\n   297→    cumulative += entry.entries;\n   298→    if (winningSlot < cumulative) {\n   299→      return { winningSlot, winner: entry.player };\n   300→    }\n   301→  }\n   302→  throw new Error(\"Failed to derive winner\");\n   303→}\n   304→\n   305→async function claimPayout(\n   306→  program: Program<Lordofrngs>,\n   307→  caller: PublicKey,\n   308→  t: TestContext,\n   309→  winnerAccount: PublicKey,\n   310→  tier = TIER_IRON,\n   311→  roundNumber = 0,\n   312→) {\n   313→  const roundPda = getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber);\n   314→  await program.methods\n   315→    .claimPayout(tier, new BN(roundNumber))\n   316→    .accounts({\n   317→      caller,\n   318→      round: roundPda,\n   319→      config: t.configPda,\n   320→      treasury: t.treasury.publicKey,\n   321→      roundCreator: t.creator,\n   322→      winnerAccount,\n   323→      randomnessAccount: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n   324→      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   325→    })\n   326→    .rpc();\n   327→}\n   328→\n   329→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   330→// Tests\n   331→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   332→describe(\"lordofrngs\", () => {\n   333→  describe(\"initialize_config\", () => {\n   334→    it(\"creates config with treasury and paused=false\", async () => {\n   335→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   336→      await initConfig(t);\n   337→\n   338→      const config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(\n   339→        t.configPda\n   340→      );\n   341→      expect(config.authority.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\n   342→      expect(config.treasury.toBase58()).to.equal(\n   343→        t.treasury.publicKey.toBase58()\n   344→      );\n   345→      expect(config.paused).to.equal(false);\n   346→      expect(config.roundCounters.map((n: any) => n.toNumber())).to.deep.equal([0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]);\n   347→    });\n   348→  });\n   349→\n   350→  describe(\"create_round\", () => {\n   351→    it(\"creates round with correct PDA data and escrow balance\", async () => {\n   352→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   353→      await initConfig(t);\n   354→\n   355→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   356→\n   357→      // Verify round state\n   358→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   359→      expect(round.tier).to.equal(TIER_IRON);\n   360→      expect(round.roundNumber.toNumber()).to.equal(0);\n   361→      expect(round.entryAmount.toNumber()).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\n   362→      expect(JSON.stringify(round.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ waiting: {} }));\n   363→      expect(round.players).to.have.length(1);\n   364→      expect(round.players[0].player.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\n   365→      expect(round.players[0].entries).to.equal(1);\n   366→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(1);\n   367→      expect(round.createdAt.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(0);\n   368→      expect(round.countdownEndsAt.toNumber()).to.equal(0);\n   369→      expect(round.lockedAt.toNumber()).to.equal(0);\n   370→      expect(round.creator.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\n   371→      expect(round.claimed).to.equal(false);\n   372→\n   373→      // Verify escrow balance: account holds rent + entry amount\n   374→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   375→      const rent = await t.context.banksClient.getRent();\n   376→      const minRent = Number(rent.minimumBalance(BigInt(roundAccount!.data.length)));\n   377→      const escrowBalance = Number(roundAccount!.lamports) - minRent;\n   378→      expect(escrowBalance).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT);\n   379→\n   380→      // Verify config round counter incremented\n   381→      const config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(t.configPda);\n   382→      expect(config.roundCounters[TIER_IRON].toNumber()).to.equal(1);\n   383→    });\n   384→\n   385→    it(\"creates round with multiple entries\", async () => {\n   386→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   387→      await initConfig(t);\n   388→\n   389→      const numEntries = 5;\n   390→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, numEntries);\n   391→\n   392→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   393→      expect(round.players[0].entries).to.equal(numEntries);\n   394→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(numEntries);\n   395→\n   396→      // Escrow should hold numEntries × entry_amount\n   397→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   398→      const rent = await t.context.banksClient.getRent();\n   399→      const minRent = Number(rent.minimumBalance(BigInt(roundAccount!.data.length)));\n   400→      const escrowBalance = Number(roundAccount!.lamports) - minRent;\n   401→      expect(escrowBalance).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * numEntries);\n   402→    });\n   403→\n   404→    it(\"increments round counter per tier\", async () => {\n   405→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   406→      await initConfig(t);\n   407→\n   408→      // Create first round (round 0)\n   409→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   410→\n   411→      // Config counter should be 1\n   412→      let config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(t.configPda);\n   413→      expect(config.roundCounters[TIER_IRON].toNumber()).to.equal(1);\n   414→\n   415→      // Create second round (round 1) — need a new PDA\n   416→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 1, 1);\n   417→\n   418→      config = await t.creatorProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(t.configPda);\n   419→      expect(config.roundCounters[TIER_IRON].toNumber()).to.equal(2);\n   420→    });\n   421→\n   422→    it(\"rejects invalid tier (tier 6)\", async () => {\n   423→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   424→      await initConfig(t);\n   425→\n   426→      const invalidTier = 6;\n   427→      const roundPda = getRoundPda(invalidTier, 0);\n   428→\n   429→      try {\n   430→        await t.creatorProgram.methods\n   431→          .createRound(invalidTier, new BN(0), 1)\n   432→          .accounts({\n   433→            creator: t.creator,\n   434→            config: t.configPda,\n   435→            round: roundPda,\n   436→            systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   437→          })\n   438→          .rpc();\n   439→        expect.fail(\"Expected InvalidTier error\");\n   440→      } catch (err) {\n   441→        // Tier 6 will cause an out-of-bounds access on round_counters[6] at\n   442→        // PDA derivation time, resulting in an Anchor error\n   443→        expect(err).to.be.instanceOf(Error);\n   444→      }\n   445→    });\n   446→\n   447→    it(\"rejects zero entries\", async () => {\n   448→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   449→      await initConfig(t);\n   450→\n   451→      const roundPda = getRoundPda(TIER_IRON, 0);\n   452→\n   453→      try {\n   454→        await t.creatorProgram.methods\n   455→          .createRound(TIER_IRON, new BN(0), 0)\n   456→          .accounts({\n   457→            creator: t.creator,\n   458→            config: t.configPda,\n   459→            round: roundPda,\n   460→            systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n   461→          })\n   462→          .rpc();\n   463→        expect.fail(\"Expected ZeroEntries error\");\n   464→      } catch (err) {\n   465→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"ZeroEntries\");\n   466→      }\n   467→    });\n   468→  });\n   469→\n   470→  describe(\"join_round\", () => {\n   471→    it(\"2nd player joins and triggers countdown (Waiting → Active)\", async () => {\n   472→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   473→      await initConfig(t);\n   474→\n   475→      // Creator starts round (player 1)\n   476→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   477→\n   478→      // Player 2 joins\n   479→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   480→\n   481→      // Verify round state\n   482→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   483→      expect(round.players).to.have.length(2);\n   484→      expect(round.players[1].player.toBase58()).to.equal(t.player2.publicKey.toBase58());\n   485→      expect(round.players[1].entries).to.equal(1);\n   486→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(2);\n   487→\n   488→      // Phase should be Active (countdown started)\n   489→      expect(JSON.stringify(round.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ active: {} }));\n   490→      expect(round.countdownEndsAt.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(0);\n   491→\n   492→      // Escrow should hold 2 × entry_amount\n   493→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   494→      const rent = await t.context.banksClient.getRent();\n   495→      const minRent = Number(rent.minimumBalance(BigInt(roundAccount!.data.length)));\n   496→      const escrowBalance = Number(roundAccount!.lamports) - minRent;\n   497→      expect(escrowBalance).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2);\n   498→    });\n   499→\n   500→    it(\"3rd player joins during Active phase without re-triggering countdown\", async () => {\n   501→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   502→      await initConfig(t);\n   503→\n   504→      const player3 = Keypair.generate();\n   505→      const player3Account = fundedAccountData();\n   506→      t.context.setAccount(player3.publicKey, player3Account);\n   507→      const player3Provider = new BankrunProvider(t.context, new Wallet(player3));\n   508→      const player3Program = new Program<Lordofrngs>(IDL, player3Provider);\n   509→\n   510→      // Creator starts round, player2 joins (triggers countdown)\n   511→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   512→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   513→\n   514→      const roundBefore = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(\n   515→        getRoundPda(TIER_IRON, 0)\n   516→      );\n   517→      const countdownBefore = roundBefore.countdownEndsAt.toNumber();\n   518→\n   519→      // Player 3 joins\n   520→      await joinRound(player3Program, player3.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   521→\n   522→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(\n   523→        getRoundPda(TIER_IRON, 0)\n   524→      );\n   525→      expect(round.players).to.have.length(3);\n   526→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(3);\n   527→      // Countdown should not have changed\n   528→      expect(round.countdownEndsAt.toNumber()).to.equal(countdownBefore);\n   529→    });\n   530→\n   531→    it(\"player can join with multiple entries\", async () => {\n   532→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   533→      await initConfig(t);\n   534→\n   535→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   536→\n   537→      // Player 2 joins with 5 entries\n   538→      const roundPda = await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda, TIER_IRON, 0, 5);\n   539→\n   540→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   541→      expect(round.players[1].entries).to.equal(5);\n   542→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(6); // 1 (creator) + 5 (player2)\n   543→\n   544→      // Escrow: 1 × amount (creator) + 5 × amount (player2)\n   545→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   546→      const rent = await t.context.banksClient.getRent();\n   547→      const minRent = Number(rent.minimumBalance(BigInt(roundAccount!.data.length)));\n   548→      const escrowBalance = Number(roundAccount!.lamports) - minRent;\n   549→      expect(escrowBalance).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 6);\n   550→    });\n   551→\n   552→    it(\"rejects duplicate player\", async () => {\n   553→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   554→      await initConfig(t);\n   555→\n   556→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   557→\n   558→      // Creator tries to join their own round again\n   559→      try {\n   560→        await joinRound(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t.configPda);\n   561→        expect.fail(\"Expected PlayerAlreadyInRound error\");\n   562→      } catch (err) {\n   563→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"PlayerAlreadyInRound\");\n   564→      }\n   565→    });\n   566→\n   567→    it(\"rejects 21st player (max 20)\", async () => {\n   568→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   569→      await initConfig(t);\n   570→\n   571→      // Creator starts round\n   572→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   573→\n   574→      // Add 19 more players (total 20)\n   575→      for (let i = 0; i < 19; i++) {\n   576→        const p = Keypair.generate();\n   577→        t.context.setAccount(p.publicKey, fundedAccountData());\n   578→        const pProvider = new BankrunProvider(t.context, new Wallet(p));\n   579→        const pProgram = new Program<Lordofrngs>(IDL, pProvider);\n   580→        await joinRound(pProgram, p.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   581→      }\n   582→\n   583→      // Verify we have 20 players\n   584→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(\n   585→        getRoundPda(TIER_IRON, 0)\n   586→      );\n   587→      expect(round.players).to.have.length(20);\n   588→\n   589→      // 21st player should be rejected\n   590→      const extra = Keypair.generate();\n   591→      t.context.setAccount(extra.publicKey, fundedAccountData());\n   592→      const extraProvider = new BankrunProvider(t.context, new Wallet(extra));\n   593→      const extraProgram = new Program<Lordofrngs>(IDL, extraProvider);\n   594→\n   595→      try {\n   596→        await joinRound(extraProgram, extra.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   597→        expect.fail(\"Expected MaxPlayersReached error\");\n   598→      } catch (err) {\n   599→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"MaxPlayersReached\");\n   600→      }\n   601→    });\n   602→\n   603→    it(\"rejects join when phase is Locked\", async () => {\n   604→      // We can't easily get to Locked phase without VRF, so we test that\n   605→      // only Waiting and Active phases are accepted. We'll simulate by\n   606→      // checking the phase validation works with a round that's in a state\n   607→      // we can't join.\n   608→      // For now, we verify the InvalidPhase error by checking that joining\n   609→      // a round that doesn't exist fails (Anchor account constraint).\n   610→      // The full phase rejection test will be covered in the start_spin tests.\n   611→\n   612→      // Instead, test that joining during Waiting phase (before 2nd player) works,\n   613→      // which is already covered above. The Locked phase test will be\n   614→      // in the start_spin + claim_payout iteration when we can create Locked rounds.\n   615→      // Skip for now — covered by the phase check in the instruction.\n   616→    });\n   617→  });\n   618→\n   619→  describe(\"buy_more_entries\", () => {\n   620→    it(\"existing player buys more entries (updated count + escrow)\", async () => {\n   621→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   622→      await initConfig(t);\n   623→\n   624→      // Creator starts round with 1 entry\n   625→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   626→\n   627→      // Creator buys 3 more entries\n   628→      await buyMoreEntries(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t.configPda, TIER_IRON, 0, 3);\n   629→\n   630→      // Verify updated state\n   631→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   632→      expect(round.players).to.have.length(1);\n   633→      expect(round.players[0].entries).to.equal(4); // 1 + 3\n   634→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(4);\n   635→\n   636→      // Escrow should hold 4 × entry_amount\n   637→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   638→      const rent = await t.context.banksClient.getRent();\n   639→      const minRent = Number(rent.minimumBalance(BigInt(roundAccount!.data.length)));\n   640→      const escrowBalance = Number(roundAccount!.lamports) - minRent;\n   641→      expect(escrowBalance).to.equal(TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 4);\n   642→    });\n   643→\n   644→    it(\"works during Active phase (after countdown starts)\", async () => {\n   645→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   646→      await initConfig(t);\n   647→\n   648→      // Creator starts round, player2 joins (triggers countdown → Active)\n   649→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   650→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   651→\n   652→      // Creator buys 2 more during Active phase\n   653→      await buyMoreEntries(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t.configPda, TIER_IRON, 0, 2);\n   654→\n   655→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   656→      expect(round.players[0].entries).to.equal(3); // 1 + 2\n   657→      expect(round.totalEntries).to.equal(4); // 3 (creator) + 1 (player2)\n   658→    });\n   659→\n   660→    it(\"rejects player not in round\", async () => {\n   661→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   662→      await initConfig(t);\n   663→\n   664→      // Creator starts round\n   665→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   666→\n   667→      // Player2 (not in round) tries to buy more\n   668→      try {\n   669→        await buyMoreEntries(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   670→        expect.fail(\"Expected PlayerNotInRound error\");\n   671→      } catch (err) {\n   672→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"PlayerNotInRound\");\n   673→      }\n   674→    });\n   675→\n   676→    it(\"rejects zero entries\", async () => {\n   677→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   678→      await initConfig(t);\n   679→\n   680→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   681→\n   682→      try {\n   683→        await buyMoreEntries(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t.configPda, TIER_IRON, 0, 0);\n   684→        expect.fail(\"Expected ZeroEntries error\");\n   685→      } catch (err) {\n   686→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"ZeroEntries\");\n   687→      }\n   688→    });\n   689→  });\n   690→\n   691→  describe(\"start_spin\", () => {\n   692→    it(\"transitions Active → Locked after countdown expires\", async () => {\n   693→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   694→      await initConfig(t);\n   695→\n   696→      // Creator creates round, player2 joins (triggers countdown → Active)\n   697→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   698→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   699→\n   700→      // Verify Active phase\n   701→      let round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   702→      expect(JSON.stringify(round.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ active: {} }));\n   703→\n   704→      // Warp past countdown\n   705→      await warpPastCountdown(t);\n   706→\n   707→      // Start spin\n   708→      await startSpin(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t);\n   709→\n   710→      // Verify Locked phase + VRF fields set\n   711→      round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(roundPda);\n   712→      expect(JSON.stringify(round.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ locked: {} }));\n   713→      expect(round.lockedAt.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(0);\n   714→      expect(round.resolveDeadline.toNumber()).to.be.greaterThan(round.lockedAt.toNumber());\n   715→      expect(round.vrfRequestKey.toBase58()).to.equal(t.mockRandomness.publicKey.toBase58());\n   716→    });\n   717→\n   718→    it(\"is idempotent (no error when already Locked)\", async () => {\n   719→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   720→      await initConfig(t);\n   721→\n   722→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   723→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   724→      await warpPastCountdown(t);\n   725→\n   726→      // First spin succeeds\n   727→      await startSpin(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t);\n   728→\n   729→      // Second spin from a different player also succeeds (idempotent no-op)\n   730→      await startSpin(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t);\n   731→\n   732→      // Still Locked\n   733→      const round = await t.creatorProgram.account.jackpotRound.fetch(\n   734→        getRoundPda(TIER_IRON, 0)\n   735→      );\n   736→      expect(JSON.stringify(round.phase)).to.equal(JSON.stringify({ locked: {} }));\n   737→    });\n   738→\n   739→    it(\"rejects spin before countdown expires\", async () => {\n   740→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   741→      await initConfig(t);\n   742→\n   743→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   744→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   745→\n   746→      // Don't warp — countdown is still running\n   747→      try {\n   748→        await startSpin(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t);\n   749→        expect.fail(\"Expected CountdownNotExpired error\");\n   750→      } catch (err) {\n   751→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"CountdownNotExpired\");\n   752→      }\n   753→    });\n   754→\n   755→    it(\"rejects spin when phase is Waiting (only 1 player)\", async () => {\n   756→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   757→      await initConfig(t);\n   758→\n   759→      await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   760→\n   761→      // Phase is Waiting — no second player joined yet\n   762→      try {\n   763→        await startSpin(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t);\n   764→        expect.fail(\"Expected InvalidPhase error\");\n   765→      } catch (err) {\n   766→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"InvalidPhase\");\n   767→      }\n   768→    });\n   769→  });\n   770→\n   771→  describe(\"claim_payout\", () => {\n   772→    /** Helper: set up a round in Locked phase (creator 1 entry, player2 1 entry) */\n   773→    async function setupLockedRound(t: TestContext, creatorEntries = 1, player2Entries = 1) {\n   774→      await initConfig(t);\n   775→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, creatorEntries);\n   776→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda, TIER_IRON, 0, player2Entries);\n   777→      await warpPastCountdown(t);\n   778→      await startSpin(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t);\n   779→      return roundPda;\n   780→    }\n   781→\n   782→    it(\"creator wins — correct payout and fee to treasury\", async () => {\n   783→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   784→      const roundPda = await setupLockedRound(t);\n   785→\n   786→      const totalEntries = 2;\n   787→      const pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * totalEntries;\n   788→      const fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   789→      const payout = pool - fee;\n   790→\n   791→      // Randomness: slot 0 → creator wins (creator owns slots [0,1), player2 owns [1,2))\n   792→      const randomness = buildRandomness(0, totalEntries);\n   793→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   794→\n   795→      const winnerBefore = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   796→      const treasuryBefore = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   797→\n   798→      await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.creator);\n   799→\n   800→      const winnerAfter = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   801→      const treasuryAfter = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   802→\n   803→      // Creator receives payout + rent refund from closed PDA (minus tx fee)\n   804→      expect(winnerAfter - winnerBefore).to.be.greaterThanOrEqual(payout);\n   805→      // Treasury receives exact fee\n   806→      expect(treasuryAfter - treasuryBefore).to.equal(fee);\n   807→    });\n   808→\n   809→    it(\"player2 wins — payout goes to player2\", async () => {\n   810→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   811→      const roundPda = await setupLockedRound(t);\n   812→\n   813→      const totalEntries = 2;\n   814→      const pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * totalEntries;\n   815→      const fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   816→      const payout = pool - fee;\n   817→\n   818→      // Randomness: slot 1 → player2 wins (creator owns [0,1), player2 owns [1,2))\n   819→      const randomness = buildRandomness(1, totalEntries);\n   820→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   821→\n   822→      const player2Before = await getBalance(t, t.player2.publicKey);\n   823→      const treasuryBefore = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   824→\n   825→      // Creator triggers claim, but payout goes to player2\n   826→      await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.player2.publicKey);\n   827→\n   828→      const player2After = await getBalance(t, t.player2.publicKey);\n   829→      const treasuryAfter = await getBalance(t, t.treasury.publicKey);\n   830→\n   831→      // Player2 receives exact payout (they didn't sign the tx, so no tx fee)\n   832→      expect(player2After - player2Before).to.equal(payout);\n   833→      expect(treasuryAfter - treasuryBefore).to.equal(fee);\n   834→    });\n   835→\n   836→    it(\"multiple entries increases win probability proportionally\", async () => {\n   837→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   838→      // Creator has 3 entries, player2 has 1 entry → 4 total\n   839→      // Creator owns slots [0,1,2), player2 owns [3)\n   840→      const roundPda = await setupLockedRound(t, 3, 1);\n   841→\n   842→      const totalEntries = 4;\n   843→      const pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * totalEntries;\n   844→      const fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   845→      const payout = pool - fee;\n   846→\n   847→      // Randomness: slot 2 → creator wins (creator owns [0,3))\n   848→      const randomness = buildRandomness(2, totalEntries);\n   849→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   850→\n   851→      const winnerBefore = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   852→      await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.creator);\n   853→      const winnerAfter = await getBalance(t, t.creator);\n   854→\n   855→      expect(winnerAfter - winnerBefore).to.be.greaterThanOrEqual(payout);\n   856→    });\n   857→\n   858→    it(\"round PDA closed after claim (account no longer exists)\", async () => {\n   859→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   860→      const roundPda = await setupLockedRound(t);\n   861→\n   862→      const randomness = buildRandomness(0, 2);\n   863→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   864→\n   865→      await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.creator);\n   866→\n   867→      // Round PDA should be closed\n   868→      const roundAccount = await t.context.banksClient.getAccount(roundPda);\n   869→      expect(roundAccount).to.be.null;\n   870→    });\n   871→\n   872→    it(\"rejects claim with unfulfilled randomness\", async () => {\n   873→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   874→      await setupLockedRound(t);\n   875→\n   876→      // Randomness stays all zeros (unfulfilled — set during context creation)\n   877→\n   878→      try {\n   879→        await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.creator);\n   880→        expect.fail(\"Expected RandomnessNotFulfilled error\");\n   881→      } catch (err) {\n   882→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\n   883→          \"RandomnessNotFulfilled\"\n   884→        );\n   885→      }\n   886→    });\n   887→\n   888→    it(\"rejects claim with wrong winner_account\", async () => {\n   889→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   890→      await setupLockedRound(t);\n   891→\n   892→      // Randomness: slot 0 → creator wins\n   893→      const randomness = buildRandomness(0, 2);\n   894→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   895→\n   896→      // Pass player2 as winner_account, but creator actually won\n   897→      try {\n   898→        await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.player2.publicKey);\n   899→        expect.fail(\"Expected NotWinner error\");\n   900→      } catch (err) {\n   901→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"NotWinner\");\n   902→      }\n   903→    });\n   904→\n   905→    it(\"rejects claim when phase is not Locked\", async () => {\n   906→      const t = await createTestContext();\n   907→      await initConfig(t);\n   908→      const roundPda = await createRound(t, TIER_IRON, 0, 1);\n   909→      await joinRound(t.player2Program, t.player2.publicKey, t.configPda);\n   910→      // Phase is Active (not Locked)\n   911→\n   912→      const randomness = buildRandomness(0, 2);\n   913→      setMockRandomness(t, randomness);\n   914→\n   915→      try {\n   916→        await claimPayout(t.creatorProgram, t.creator, t, t.creator);\n   917→        expect.fail(\"Expected InvalidPhase error\");\n   918→      } catch (err) {\n   919→        expect((err as AnchorError).error.errorCode.code).to.equal(\"InvalidPhase\");\n   920→      }\n   921→    });\n   922→  });\n   923→});\n   924→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PkGv76FLY3F3ZJ9SxMw5wX","session_id":"d3bf4c03-8136-45c3-a2a1-9d51b20ea4ea","uuid":"64238995-095d-4d61-a720-2db5b0561421"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PkGv76FLY3F3ZJ9SxMw5wX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete bankrun test file for the lordofrngs program:\n\n## File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts`\n\n### Key Test Helpers & Infrastructure\n\n**PDA Helpers:**\n- `getConfigPda()` - derives config PDA with seed `\"lord_config\"`\n- `getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber)` - derives round PDA with seeds `\"jackpot_round\"`, tier byte, and round number\n\n**Test Context Factory:**\n- `createTestContext()` - creates a complete test setup with:\n  - Creator (default payer)\n  - Treasury account (for fees)\n  - Player 2 (second player)\n  - Mock Orao VRF accounts (mockRandomness, mockOraoProgram, mockOraoNetworkState, mockOraoTreasury)\n  - All accounts pre-funded with 100 SOL\n  - Mock randomness account initialized with all zeros (unfulfilled state)\n\n**Clock Manipulation:**\n- `warpPastCountdown(t)` - advances blockchain time by `COUNTDOWN_SECONDS + 10` (70 seconds total)\n\n**Instruction Helpers:**\n- `initConfig(t)` - initializes config with treasury\n- `createRound(t, tier?, roundNumber?, numEntries?, creator?)` - creates a round with creator as first player\n- `joinRound(program, player, configPda, tier?, roundNumber?, numEntries?)` - joins an existing round\n- `buyMoreEntries(program, player, configPda, tier?, roundNumber?, numEntries?)` - adds entries to existing player\n- `startSpin(program, caller, t, tier?, roundNumber?)` - triggers VRF request and transitions to Locked phase\n- `claimPayout(program, caller, t, winnerAccount, tier?, roundNumber?)` - claims winner payout and closes round\n\n**Randomness & Balance Helpers:**\n- `setMockRandomness(t, buffer)` - sets the mock VRF response (32 bytes)\n- `getBalance(t, pubkey)` - retrieves account lamports\n- `buildRandomness(winningSlot, totalEntries)` - constructs randomness buffer where first 8 bytes mod totalEntries yields winningSlot\n- `deriveWinner(randomness, totalEntries, players)` - mirrors on-chain logic to determine winner from randomness\n\n**Constants:**\n- `TIER_IRON = 0`, `TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000` (0.005 SOL)\n- `COUNTDOWN_SECONDS = 60`\n- `TOTAL_FEE_BPS = 300` (3%)\n- `RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED` - zero buffer for unfulfilled VRF state\n\n### Test Coverage (Existing)\n\nThe file has tests for:\n- `initialize_config` (1 test)\n- `create_round` (4 tests covering: basic creation, multiple entries, counter increments, invalid tier, zero entries)\n- `join_round` (5 tests covering: trigger countdown, no re-trigger on 3rd player, multiple entries, duplicate player rejection, max 20 players)\n- `buy_more_entries` (4 tests)\n- `start_spin` (3 tests covering: phase transition, idempotency, pre-expiry rejection, Waiting phase rejection)\n- `claim_payout` (7 tests covering: creator wins, player2 wins, multiple entries, PDA closure, unfulfilled randomness rejection, wrong winner rejection, non-Locked phase rejection)\n\nThis infrastructure is ready for `timeout_refund` tests. You would need to add:\n- A helper function for triggering the timeout refund (likely similar to `startSpin` but calling a `timeout_refund` instruction)\n- Tests verifying refunds go to correct players, escrow is distributed, PDA is closed, etc."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aafe2a3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40506\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 13149</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3bf4c03-8136-45c3-a2a1-9d51b20ea4ea","uuid":"888dae6e-06fc-4b09-b20f-f949ec34605e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read and return the FULL contents of `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` - this is the bankrun test file for the lordofrngs program. I need to see all existing test helpers and infrastructure to add timeout_refund tests.","agentId":"aafe2a3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete bankrun test fil